parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure (CVT Slipping, Jerking, and Loss of Power)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, jerk, and slip, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can also lead to a loss of acceleration, making it difficult to merge or cross traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates
jerks
and fails to properly shift gears
the transmission slips repeatedly
the vehicle loses power and will not accelerate
the engine light comes on with codes such as P0746
and P0868.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the keyless entry system can cause the vehicle to fail to start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The key fob battery is drained
the "no key" message is displayed
the vehicle fails to start
the vehicle starts but then stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electronic sliding doors can cause physical harm to occupants or bystanders, as the doors may not stop or retreat when obstructed.
symptoms: The sliding doors do not stop or retreat when obstructed
the doors push occupants or bystanders with full force
the doors can only be stopped by quickly pushing the door open/close button.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical systems suddenly power off
including steering
lights
and brakes
the vehicle slowly comes to a stop
the fuel gauge shows 1/4 tank and the trip computer shows 60 miles left
the issue resolves after refueling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The tailgate opening by itself can cause unexpected noise, alarm activation, and potentially lead to theft or loss of cargo. When the tailgate opens while the vehicle is in motion, it can create a hazardous situation, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The tailgate opens unexpectedly while the vehicle is stationary or in motion
the alarm system is activated
the tailgate opens at low speeds (around 5mph).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic sliding doors to stop and retreat when a person is present in the opening can cause significant injury, especially to young children.
symptoms: The electronic sliding doors continue to exert force and move a person
even when they are present in the opening
the doors do not adequately stop and retreat
the doors can move a person one to two steps sideways.
